Sub: Agree't - City County of
San Francisco - Lomita Park
FORM 200
SOUTHERN PACIFIC COMPANY
(PACIFIC LINES)
LOCAL
E. R. ANTHONY.
SUPERINTENDENT
THIRD AND TOWNSEND STREETS
SAN FRANCISCO, CALIF.
March 22nd, 1927.
Mr.
Joseph J.
Phillips, Right of Way Agent,
The City & County of
San Francisco,
Room 375,
City
Hall,
San Francisco, California.
Dear Sir:
Referring to your letter March 19th, 1927, making
application for permission to cross under Southern Pacific
Company's tracks and right of way near Lomita Park, Calif.,
with a 3-inch wrought iron water pipe, for purpose of serving
air port to be located at that point:
I am attaching hereto duplicate counterparts of
proposed agreement covering. If satisfactory, kindly have
both copies executed by proper officers of the City and
County of San Francisco, corporate seal affixed, insert date
of execution in
space provided and return original cunterpart
to this office for filing.
Duplicate counterpart of agreement has been fully
executed on, the part of Southern Pacific Company and is to
be retained in your file.
Yours truly,
cambass
superintendent
